   <refnamediv>
       <refname>packr</refname>
               <refpurpose>deletes rows of a matrix containing missing values </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>mat=packr(mat)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> mat </term> =    a (n x p) matrix</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> mat </term> =    a (m x p) matrix</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Function that mimics gauss function packr: deletes the rows of a matrix that contain any missing values.

        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
v=[ones(7,1) [1:7]'] ;v(3,2)=%nan;w= packr(v)// returns:
// w  =//!   1.    1. !//!   1.    2. !//!   1.    4. !//!   1.    5. !//!   1.    6. !//!   1.    7. !  

               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
